20/*
21Functions for basic LZ77 compression and utilities for the "squeeze" LZ77
22compression.
23*/
24
25#ifndef ZOPFLI_LZ77_H_
26#define ZOPFLI_LZ77_H_
27
28#include <stdlib.h>
29
30#include "cache.h"
31#include "hash.h"
32#include "zopfli.h"
33
34/*
35Stores lit/length and dist pairs for LZ77.
36litlens: Contains the literal symbols or length values.
37dists: Indicates the distance, or 0 to indicate that there is no distance and
38litlens contains a literal instead of a length.
39litlens and dists both have the same size.
40*/
41typedef struct ZopfliLZ77Store {
42 unsigned short* litlens; /* Lit or len. */
43 unsigned short* dists; /* If 0: indicates literal in corresponding litlens,
44 if > 0: length in corresponding litlens, this is the distance. */
45 size_t size;
46} ZopfliLZ77Store;
47
48void ZopfliInitLZ77Store(ZopfliLZ77Store* store);
49void ZopfliCleanLZ77Store(ZopfliLZ77Store* store);
50void ZopfliCopyLZ77Store(const ZopfliLZ77Store* source, ZopfliLZ77Store* dest);
51void ZopfliStoreLitLenDist(unsigned short length, unsigned short dist,
52 ZopfliLZ77Store* store);
53
54/*
55Some state information for compressing a block.
56This is currently a bit under-used (with mainly only the longest match cache),
57but is kept for easy future expansion.
58*/
59typedef struct ZopfliBlockState {
60 const ZopfliOptions* options;
61
62#ifdef ZOPFLI_LONGEST_MATCH_CACHE
63 /* Cache for length/distance pairs found so far. */
64 ZopfliLongestMatchCache* lmc;
65#endif
66
67 /* The start (inclusive) and end (not inclusive) of the current block. */
68 size_t blockstart;
69 size_t blockend;
70} ZopfliBlockState;
71
72/*
73Finds the longest match (length and corresponding distance) for LZ77
74compression.
75Even when not using "sublen", it can be more efficient to provide an array,
76because only then the caching is used.
77array: the data
78pos: position in the data to find the match for
79size: size of the data
80limit: limit length to maximum this value (default should be 258). This allows
81 finding a shorter dist for that length (= less extra bits). Must be
82 in the range [ZOPFLI_MIN_MATCH, ZOPFLI_MAX_MATCH].
83sublen: output array of 259 elements, or null. Has, for each length, the
84 smallest distance required to reach this length. Only 256 of its 259 values
85 are used, the first 3 are ignored (the shortest length is 3. It is purely
86 for convenience that the array is made 3 longer).
87*/
88void ZopfliFindLongestMatch(
89 ZopfliBlockState *s, const ZopfliHash* h, const unsigned char* array,
90 size_t pos, size_t size, size_t limit,
91 unsigned short* sublen, unsigned short* distance, unsigned short* length);
92
93/*
94Verifies if length and dist are indeed valid, only used for assertion.
95*/
96void ZopfliVerifyLenDist(const unsigned char* data, size_t datasize, size_t pos,
97 unsigned short dist, unsigned short length);
98
99/*
100Counts the number of literal, length and distance symbols in the given lz77
101arrays.
102litlens: lz77 lit/lengths
103dists: ll77 distances
104start: where to begin counting in litlens and dists
105end: where to stop counting in litlens and dists (not inclusive)
106ll_count: count of each lit/len symbol, must have size 288 (see deflate
107 standard)
108d_count: count of each dist symbol, must have size 32 (see deflate standard)
109*/
110void ZopfliLZ77Counts(const unsigned short* litlens,
111 const unsigned short* dists,
112 size_t start, size_t end,
113 size_t* ll_count, size_t* d_count);
114
115/*
116Does LZ77 using an algorithm similar to gzip, with lazy matching, rather than
117with the slow but better "squeeze" implementation.
118The result is placed in the ZopfliLZ77Store.
119If instart is larger than 0, it uses values before instart as starting
120dictionary.
121*/
122void ZopfliLZ77Greedy(ZopfliBlockState* s, const unsigned char* in,
123 size_t instart, size_t inend,
124 ZopfliLZ77Store* store);
125
126#endif /* ZOPFLI_LZ77_H_ */
